Sec. 148.026. LIEN. (a) To secure all or part of the sales
price, a person who sells cattle, sheep, goats, or hogs for slaughter
has a lien on each animal sold and on the carcass of the animal,
products from the animal, and proceeds from the sale of the animal,
its carcass, or its products.
(b) A lien under this section is attached and perfected on
delivery of the livestock to the purchaser without further action.
The lien continues as to the animal, its carcass, its products, and
the proceeds of any sale without regard to possession by the party
entitled to the lien.
Acts 1981, 67th Leg., p. 1388, ch. 388, Sec. 1, eff. Sept. 1, 1981.

